<P/>
-------EOD-------
Now, 
<D>
V(Z) = V(Y) + V(\beta X) - 2cov(Y,\beta X) = V(Y) + \beta^2 V(X)
- 2 \beta cov(X,Y).
</D>
Since <M>\beta = [[cov(X,Y)][V(X)]],</M> this reduces to 
<D>
V(Y) - [[cov(X,Y)^2][V(X)]].
</D>
Since this is <M>\geq0,</M> the inequality follows immediately.
<P/>
-------EOD-------

-------EOD-------

Thus, if we take <M>a=-\beta</M>, <M>b = 1</M>  and <M>c = k</M>, then 
<M>P(aX+bY=c)=1</M>, as
 required, completing the proof.
-------EOD-------
